         <abstract>
            <p>A new framework for determining the relative contributions of active asset allocation and stock selection to portfolio return is based on an allocation process that includes ex ante target active returns for stock selection. These target returns can be used to calculate a precise breakdown of the interaction effect between active asset allocation and stock selection. This breakdown is particularly valuable in allowing a better understanding of the value added by each part of the investment process.</p>
          </abstract>
